The '''Centre for Cognitive Ageing and Cognitive Epidemiology''' (CCACE) is a "centre of excellence" to advance research into how ageing affects cognition, and how mental ability in youth affects health and longevity.
Based at the [[University of Edinburgh]] and funded by the [[Medical Research Council (UK)|Medical Research Council]] (MRC), [[ESRC]], [[BBSRC]] and [[EPSRC]] through the LLHW MRC's Lifelong Health and Wellbeing scheme, the Centre is led by [[Ian Deary|Professor Ian Deary]] alongside 2 co-Directors and 8 Research Group Leaders spread across three University of Edinburgh sites ([[George Square, Edinburgh|George Square]], New Royal Infirmary of Edinburgh, [[Western General Hospital]]).
==External links== *[http://www.ccace.ed.ac.uk Centre for Cognitive Ageing and Cognitive Epidemiology (CCACE) official website]
